        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:55PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Briggsdale, or 30 miles northeast of Greeley, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Briggsdale.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
